	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" /><div class="quotetitle">Jedi QuestMaster wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">If four power pads would work I take it 4 zappers would work?</div>
<br />
<br />The zapper light/trigger detect is directly connected, but with the controllers and power pad it is a stream of serial bits.  Different enough to require a select switch on the Satellite.
<br />
<br />Well, I looked up the manual:
<br />"* The NES Four Score cannot be used with the NES Zapper (R) or NES Power Pad (R)."
<br /><a href="http://www.nesworld.com/manuals/fourscor.txt" class="postlink">http://www.nesworld.com/manuals/fourscor.txt</a>
<br />
<br />Damn, there goes the idea for the "COPS" game where you use a powerpad, zapper, and powerglove all at once.
<br />
<br />With 4 powerpads, you could make a small power-padded room where you could jump Mario-style and hit the ceiling.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


